--------------------
--  Introduction  --
--------------------

libdialplan provides a data structure as well as query and I/O routines for
dial-plans for reception management.

Currently the only supported storage format for dial-plans is XML files.

libdialplan is GPLv3, see COPYING3 and COPYING.RUNTIME.

--------------------
--  Dependencies  --
--------------------

libdialplan depends on XMLAda[1] and any Ada 2012[2] compiler.

--------------------
--  Installation  --
--------------------

You build and install libdialplan using this sequence of commands:

   ./configure
   make install

If you want to override the installation location, you can do it with the
variables PREFIX and DESTDIR.

The 'install' target in the makefile uses 'sudo install' as the default
command to install files.  This can be overridden with the INSTALL variable.

-----------
--  Use  --
-----------

Include a 'with "libdialplan";' in your GNAT project file and you should be
set.

------------------
--  References  --
------------------

If you want to find other free Ada tools or libraries AdaIC [3] is an
excellent starting point.

[1] XMLAda
    http://libre.adacore.com/tools/xmlada/
    SVN: svn checkout http://svn.eu.adacore.com/anonsvn/Dev/trunk/xmlada/

[2] Ada 2012 Reference Manual
    http://ada-auth.org/arm.html

[3] Free Ada Tools and Libraries:
    http://www.adaic.org/ada-resources/tools-libraries/
